The paper discusses entity resolution, which is a common problem in databases and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions metrics borrowed from multi-class classification and clustering domains, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the empirical results of different evaluation metrics, which may be of interest to researchers in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
